messages.content: What is the purpose of comfyui-self-guidance?
Comfyui-self-guidance is an unofficial ComfyUI implementation of Diffusion Self-Guidance for Controllable Image Generation, allowing users to perform spatial manipulation of objects in real images.
To install comfyui-self-guidance, clone the repo into the custom_nodes folder or use the Manager.
Which models are currently supported by comfyui-self-guidance?
Currently, only SD series models are supported by comfyui-self-guidance.
In the first example of the comfyui-self-guidance workflow, what are the target and fix objects?
In the first example, the target object is set to 'carrot' and the fix object is set to 'onion'.
What scale factors are used in the first example of the comfyui-self-guidance workflow?
In the first example, the scale factors used are 0.8 for shrinking and 1.3 for enlarging the target object.
In the second example of the comfyui-self-guidance workflow, what are the target and fix objects?
In the second example, the target object is set to 'eclair' and the fix object is set to 'coffee'.
What scale factors are used in the second example of the comfyui-self-guidance workflow?
In the second example, the scale factors used are 0.8 for shrinking and 1.3 for enlarging the target object.
